    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Voice in the Dark</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas Rogers comments on Daniel Pinkwater's reflections on Jean Shepherd's masterful radio storytelling (Jan 2)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Daniel Pinkwater's reflections on Jean Shepherd's masterful radio storytelling released a memory: my older brother and I, two South Bronx teenagers in the 1960's, huddled under the covers in the twin bed we shared in our family's four-room tenement apartment. A transistor radio conjured Shepherd's raspy voice and brought us his charm and laughter. Here we found an adult who loved life.</p>
        <p>Thomas Rogers  Tucson</p>
      </block>
